data.enText: remaining at the end of a process

data.chText: 电脑程序还有一些残留问题。
data.enText: There are still a few residual problems with the computer program.

tr: (often plural) a payment that is made to a performer or writer or director of a television show or commercial that is paid for every repeat showing
example: he could retire on his residuals

tr: something left after other parts have been taken away
example: he took what he wanted and I got the balance

tr: relating to or indicating a remainder

value.def: Residual is used to describe what remains of something when most of it has gone.

example.tran: 核武器实验后残留的辐射

example.ex: Turn the hotplate off and allow the residual heat to keep the mixture simmering.
example.tran: 把烤盘关掉，让余热把混合物再煨一下。
